Debugging this program on the IBM 5.0 VM with a NullPointerException configured to "not stop in the ThrowsNPE class" (configured on the breakpoint property filters page), causes the VM to suspend at a NullPointerException.

public class ThrowsNPE {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		ThrowsNPE anObject = new ThrowsNPE();
		try {
			anObject.throwBaby();
		} catch(NullPointerException ne) {
			// do nothing
		}		
		anObject.throwBaby();
	}


	public void throwBaby() {
		throw new NullPointerException();
	}
}

The VM is suspended at java.lang.Class.isAssignableFrom(java.lang.Class) - which is a native method.

The problem does not happen if the exception filter is "inclusive" rather than "exclusive". This appears to be a VM bug with IBM 5.0 VMs. You should file a bug with the appropriate IBM team.
